# Ralph Environment Variables
# Copy this file to $HOME/.ralph-env or scripts/ralph/.ralph-env and fill in your values.
# This file is NOT tracked by git.

# --- To use a consolidated provider (e.g., OpenRouter) ---
# Uncomment the following lines to route all harnesses through OpenRouter.
# This provides a single API key to access multiple model providers.
# export OPENAI_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-or-..."   # Your OpenRouter API key
# export ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-or-..." # Same key works for Anthropic-compatible endpoint

# --- To use native providers (automatic fallback on failure) ---
# Alternatively, you can set the following *_NATIVE variables to enable automatic fallback 
# if the consolidated provider fails (e.g., due to quota exhaustion or errors).
# On fallback:
#   * Base URL overrides (OPENAI_BASE_URL, ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL) will be unset, 
#     allowing harnesses to use their default endpoints
#   * API keys will be set to the *_NATIVE values if defined, otherwise unset
#     (unset allows harness-configured authentication like OAuth or auth files)
# If set, these variables will be used on the second attempt if the first attempt fails.
# 
# For Codex fallback to OpenAI native API:
#   export OPENAI_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-..."   # Your OpenAI API key
#
# For Claude Code fallback to Anthropic native API:
#   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-ant-..." # Your Anthropic API key
#
# For Opencode and PI Agent fallback to Opencode Zen Setup:
#   export OPENCODE_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-op-..."   # Your Opencode Zen API key
#   (This will be available as OPENCODE_API_KEY during fallback for both harnesses)
#
# --- Optional: Provider-specific overrides per harness ---
# If a harness requires different variables, set them here.
# Example for Opencode (if it uses distinct vars):
# export OPENTCODE_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export OPENTCODE_API_KEY="sk-or-..."
# Example for PI Agent:
# export PI_BASE_URL="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1"
# export PI_API_KEY="sk-or-..."

# --- Fallback Note ---
# The system will automatically fall back as described above when the first attempt 
# to execute a story with the configured harness (e.g., pointing to OpenRouter) fails.
# To enable this feature, set the *_NATIVE variables as described above.
# If you do not set the *_NATIVE variables, no automatic fallback will occur.
# You can also manage fallback manually by unsetting the base URL variables (OPENAI_BASE_URL, ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL) 
# and ensuring your desired API keys (OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENCODE_API_KEY) 
# are set in the environment (unset API key variables allow harness-configured auth).
# 
# Examples:
#   # To fall back to native OpenAI/Anthropic API keys:
#   export OPENAI_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-..."
#   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-ant-..."
#
#   # To fall back to Opencode Zen Setup for Opencode and PI Agent:
#   export OPENCODE_API_KEY_NATIVE="sk-op-..."
#
#   # To rely on externally configured authentication (OAuth, auth files, etc.):
#   # Leave all *_NATIVE variables unset
